Defendant in custody.
Count 1, possess cocaine with intent to deliver - 
Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for six (6) years.  Three (3) years initial confinement followed by three (3) years extended supervision.  
Defendant is found eligible for the Challenge Incarceration Program and the Substance Abuse Program after serving the first 18 months of initial confinement.
Conditions of extended supervision:
1)  Maintain absolute sobriety;
2)  Random drug screens and pays for same;
3)  No association with any known drug users or gang members;
4)  Obtain and maintain full-time employment;
5)  Follow all rules of community supervision;
6)  Complete 400 hours of community service during the term of extended supervision;
7)  Submit a DNA sample and pay surcharge;
8)  Pay costs of the action; and 
9)  Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC.
Defendant is to be given 49 days jail credit.
Minutes.
